        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">10</P><P>A well played wizard makes exp groups in the 50s go twice as fast as a group without. Nothing really can take huge chunks out of a MOBs life like a wizzie can. They also can stop mobs that haven't been snared by just obliterating them. Also when times get tough, a wizzie can manaburn and do almost all the work when you have 5+ adds that you didn't want.</P><P>Outside of that, raidwise Wizzies are a needed class for anything involving dragons and beyond. It's a fact, you NEED wizards. You can't honestly say that about the other 3 int pure caster classes. You can skimp on a chanter and stick with shaman speeds, and use root parking - You can fight your way to a mob instead of having a mage CoH you - You can bring more clerics to manage mana more efficiently (Or mod rod)instead of using a Necro. But you can't skimp on Wizards, ever.<BR>Yes, it sounds crazy about no chanters etc if you're going to do such high end raids, but believe me, ive been through so many ghetto-rigged raids you really can get by with most classes like this, but never without a wizzzzzzzzzzzzzzz. Esp now with the Dragonbane and Giantbane.</P><P><BR>Edited by - xaen on 10/20/2001  00:54:28<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
